%META:TOPICINFO{author="PeterThoeny" date="1007404200" format="1.0" version="1.21"}%
*%WIKITOOLNAME% Site-Level Preferences*
d8 1
a8 1
The following settings are __site-level preferences__ , e.g. affecting all users in all %WIKITOOLNAME% webs. These preferences can be overwritten by __web preferences__ (topic %WEBPREFSTOPIC% in each %WIKITOOLNAME% web) and __user preferences__ (your personal topic, i.e. Main.TWikiGuest in the %WIKITOOLNAME%.%MAINWEB% web)
d10 1
a10 3
__Preferences:__

	* List of %WIKITOOLNAME% webs: (the first line of a topic; to add a web see TWikiDocumentation and TWikiWebsTable)
d12 1
a12 1
		* __Note:__ To automatically list all non-hidden webs in alphabetical order you can use this variable instead: Set WIKIWEBLIST = %WEBLIST{"[[$name.%HOMETOPIC%][$name]]" separator=" %SEP% "}%
d14 1
a14 1
	* List of topics of a web: (the second line of a topic, is overwritten by web preferences)
d52 1
a52 1
		* __Note:__ Keyword =$name= gets expanded to filename; =$comment= to comment; =\t= to tab (3 spaces for bullets).
d55 4
a58 3
		* Set ATTACHEDIMAGEFORMAT = \t* $comment: <br /> <img src="%ATTACHURLPATH%/$name" alt="$name" $size />
		* __Note:__ Above image is shown as broken, it gets expanded correctly when you attach an image.
		* __Note:__ Keyword =$name= gets expanded to filename; =$comment= to comment; =$size= to =width="..." height="..."= attribute of =img= tag; =\t= to tab (3 spaces for bullets).
d60 1
a60 1
	* Wiki webmaster email address:
d63 1
a63 1
	* Mail host for outgoing mail. This is used for WebChangesAlert if Perl module ==Net::SMTP== is installed. If not, or if =SMTPMAILHOST= is empty, the external sendmail program is used instead (defined by ==$mailProgram== in ==TWiki.cfg==). Examples: =mail.your.company= or =localhost=
d66 1
a66 1
	* Mail domain sending mail. SMTP requires that you identify the TWiki server sending mail. If not set, ==Net::SMTP== will guess it for you. Examples: =twiki.your.company=
d69 2
d75 3
a77 1
		* __Note:__ In case you have a rough plugin you can disable all plugins with the ==$disableAllPlugins== flag in the =TWiki.cfg= file.
d79 1
a79 1
	* http-equiv meta tags for __view__, __rdiff__, __attach__, __search*__ scripts:
d84 1
a84 1
	* http-equiv meta tags for __edit__ script. Example to expire immediately: <br> =Set HTTP_EQUIV_ON_EDIT = &lt;meta http-equiv="Expires" content="%<nop>GMTIME{"$day $month, $year - $hour:$min:$sec"}% GMT"&gt;=
d89 1
a89 1
	* http-equiv meta tags for __preview__ script:
d94 3
a96 1
	* Users or groups allowed to change or rename this <nop>%TOPIC% topic: (I.e. %MAINWEB%.TWikiAdminGroup)
d103 9
d113 1
a113 7
__Notes:__
	* A preference is defined as: <br> =6 spaces * Set NAME = value= <br> Example:
		* S<nop>et WEBBGCOLOR = #FFFFC0
	* Preferences are used as %TWIKIWEB%.TWikiVariables by enclosing the name in percent signs. Example:
		* When you write variable =%WEB<nop>BGCOLOR%= , it gets expanded to =%WEBBGCOLOR%= .
	* The sequential order of the preference settings is significant. Define preferences that use other preferences first, i.e. set =<nop>WEBCOPYRIGHT= before =<nop>WIKIWEBMASTER= since =%<nop>WEBCOPYRIGHT%= uses the =%<nop>WIKIWEBMASTER%= variable.
	* You can introduce new variables and use them in your topics and templates. There is no need to change the %WIKITOOLNAME% engine (Perl scripts).
a114 1
__Related Topics:__
